==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frankincense
<hw>Frank"in*cense</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>franc</ets> free, pure + <ets>encens</ets> incense.]</ety> <def>A
fragrant, aromatic resin, or gum resin, burned as an incense in
religious rites or for medicinal fumigation. The best kinds now come
from East Indian trees, of the genus <gen>Boswellia</gen>; a commoner
sort, from the Norway spruce (<spn>Abies excelsa</spn>) and other
coniferous trees. The frankincense of the ancient Jews is still
unidentified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Franking</ent>⟦br⟧
